**Smart Enumerations in DDD C#**

Smart enumerations are a design pattern used in Domain-Driven Design (DDD) to create a robust and maintainable enumeration system. They provide a way to encapsulate enumeration values and behavior within a single class.

**Example Implementation**

Let's create a simple example of a smart enumeration for a `PaymentMethod` in a e-commerce application.

```csharp
public enum PaymentMethodEnum
{
    CreditCard,
    PayPal,
    BankTransfer
}

public class PaymentMethod
{
    private readonly PaymentMethodEnum _value;

    private PaymentMethod(PaymentMethodEnum value)
    {
        _value = value;
    }

    public static PaymentMethod CreditCard => new PaymentMethod(PaymentMethodEnum.CreditCard);
    public static PaymentMethod PayPal => new PaymentMethod(PaymentMethodEnum.PayPal);
    public static PaymentMethod BankTransfer => new PaymentMethod(PaymentMethodEnum.BankTransfer);

    public bool IsCreditCard => _value == PaymentMethodEnum.CreditCard;
    public bool IsPayPal => _value == PaymentMethodEnum.PayPal;
    public bool IsBankTransfer => _value == PaymentMethodEnum.BankTransfer;

    public override string ToString() => _value.ToString();
}
```

